# Quantitative Portfolio Management System

A Python-based quantitative finance system that simulates institutional portfolio management workflows including data ingestion, feature engineering, strategy generation, backtesting, portfolio construction, and performance analysis.

---

## Features

- Market data pipeline using Yahoo Finance
- Feature engineering (returns, volatility, momentum, z-score)
- Trading strategies (Momentum, Mean Reversion, Trend Following)
- Backtesting engine with transaction costs
- Portfolio construction (equal-weight allocation)
- Performance metrics (Sharpe ratio, drawdown, returns)
- Equity curve visualization

---

## Tech Stack

- Python
- Pandas, NumPy
- Matplotlib
- yFinance
- Scikit-learn (optional extensions)

---

## Example Output

- Portfolio equity curve
- Strategy performance metrics
- Multi-asset backtesting results

---

## Future Improvements

- Risk parity portfolio optimization
- Mean-variance optimization (Markowitz)
- Value at Risk (VaR) & CVaR
- Interactive dashboard (Plotly / Streamlit)
- Machine learning alpha models

